he conservator (Chicago, Ill.), December 18, 1886", "type": ["issue"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/sn84024048/1886-12-18/ed-1/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/sn83045487/", "http://lccn.loc.gov/sn83045487", "https://search.catalog.loc.gov/instances/6c2dc1c7-67e7-5162-bfe2-77119f83478a"], "batch": ["iune_delta_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["sandburg, carl"], "date": "1911", "description": ["Daily (except Sunday and holidays), Nov. 28, 1912-July 6, 1917 Began in 1911. -v. 6, no. 237 (July 6, 1917). \"An adless daily newspaper.\" Saturdays have Noon and Final editions, Dec. 28, 1912-June 21, 1913; Saturdays have Noon and Last editions, June 28, 1913-<Dec. 13, 1913>; began issuing daily Noon and Last editions, Dec. 20, 1913-July 6, 1917. Issues for <May 7-17, 1915> called also \"Moving Picture Edition.\" Vol. 5, no. 36 (Nov. 6, 1915) issue called also \"Garment Workers' Special Edition.\" Issues have no page numbering. Volume numbering begins with Nov. 20, 1911 issue. Issue for <Nov. 24, 1911> lacks vol., no., and chronological designation. Issue for Nov. 4, 1911 erroneously designated as Oct. 4, 1911. Issue for v. 3, no. 290 (Sept. 7, 1914) erroneously designated as v. 3, no. 300 (Sept. 7, 1914). The error in numbering continues. Issue for v. 5, no. 7 (Oct. 5, 1915) erroneously designated as v. 5, no. 7 (Sept. 5, 1915). Issue for v. 5, no. 214 (June 7, 1916) erroneously designated as v. 5, no. 214 (June 6, 1916). Available on microfilm; Library of Congress, Photoduplication Service. Archived issues are available in digital format as part of the Library of Congress Chronicling America online collection. Description based on: Nov. 1, 1911."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-06-05T18:25:14.142Z", "group": ["newspaper-titles", "ndnp/newspapers", "catalog-split-08", "catalog", "united-states-newspaper-directory", "main-catalog-split-08"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn83045487/", "image_url": [], "index": 31, "language": ["english"], "latlong": [41.883229, -87.632398], "location": ["illinois", "united states", "chicago", "cook county"], "location_str": "", "lonlat": [-87.632398, 41.883229], "number": ["wisconsin hist soc, newsp proj", "2163-7121", "library of congress", "chicago hist soc libr", "original", "1", "northwestern univ", "2069", "sn97062043", "microfilm master", "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn83045487/1911-11-01/ed-1/", "2025-05-12t17:27:14.722511", "microfilm service copy", "9493999", "sn83045487", "online resource", "2026-04-13t21:30:13", "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn83045487/1917-07-06/ed-1/", "2025-07-29t10:49:56.200000"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["chronicling america", "catalog", "serial and government publications division", "the day book (chicago, ill.) 1911-1917", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries"], "publication_frequency": ["daily"], "score": 45.590534, "shelf_id": "Newspaper", "site": ["chroniclingamerica", "usnd", "catalog"], "subject": ["united states", "chicago", "newspapers", "chicago (ill.)", "illinois", "cook county"], "timestamp": "2026-07-22T07:33:38.567Z", "title": "The day book", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/sn83045487/"}], "next_resource": {"label": "Next Issue", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn83045487/1913-12-15/ed-1/?fo=json&sp=1"}, "options": {"access_group": [""], "access_group_raw": "", "all": null, "api_version": "1", "app_context": null, "application_version": "$Revision$", "attribute": null, "attribute!": null, "attribute_map": null, "cache_tags": ["ndnp/iune", "university-of-illinois-at-urbana-champaign-library-urbana-il-awardee", "ndnp/dlc-2020_now", "library-of-congress-washington-dc-awardee-8", "newspaper-titles", "ndnp/newspapers", "catalog-split-08", "catalog", "united-states-newspaper-directory", "main-catalog-split-08", "catalog-split-13", "main-catalog-split-13", "main-catalog", "catalog-split-10", "fsa", "main-catalog-split-10", "fsa-o